TITLE: Creating an Express Server for React Server Components
DESCRIPTION: Express server setup for rendering React Server Components. Uses renderRequest from @parcel/rsc/node to render the page component as HTML in response to requests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parcel-bundler/website/blob/v2/src/recipes/rsc.md#2025-04-09_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import express from "express";
import { renderRequest } from "@parcel/rsc/node";
import { Page } from "./Page";

// Create an Express app and serve the dist folder.
const app = express();
app.use("/client", express.static("dist/client"));

// Create a route for the home page.
app.get("/", async (req, res) => {
  await renderRequest(req, res, <Page />, { component: Page });
});

app.listen(3000);
```

