TITLE: Advanced Hot Module Replacement with State Management
DESCRIPTION: A more advanced implementation of Hot Module Replacement that preserves state between module reloads. It uses dispose to save data before a module is replaced and accept to restore that data when the module is updated.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parcel-bundler/website/blob/v2/src/features/development.md#2025-04-09_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
if (module.hot) {
  module.hot.dispose(function (data) {
    // module is about to be replaced.
    // You can save data that should be accessible to the new asset in `data`
    data.updated = Date.now();
  });

  module.hot.accept(function (getParents) {
    // module or one of its dependencies was just updated.
    // data stored in `dispose` is available in `module.hot.data`
    let { updated } = module.hot.data;
  });
}
```

