TITLE: Implementing Content Hashing in Parcel Namer Plugin (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to include a content hash in the bundle filename using the hashReference property. It checks the needsStableName property to determine whether to include the hash, ensuring compatibility with dependencies that require consistent filenames.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parcel-bundler/website/blob/v2/src/plugin-system/namer.md#2025-04-09_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import {Namer} from '@parcel/plugin';

export default new Namer({
  name({bundle}) {
    let name = yourNamingFunction(bundle);
    if (!bundle.needsStableName) {
      name += "." + bundle.hashReference;
    }
    return name + "." + bundle.type;
  }
});
```

